        {
          "role": "assistant",
          "content": "I know. It feels like everything's spinning right now. Your brother made a terrible choice, but he's still your brother. And you're trying to do what's right — that matters. Let's just sit with this for a moment. You don't have to have all the answers. Just breathe. I'm here."
        },
        {
          "role": "user",
          "content": "okay. talk me through it. what do i actually do that doesn't make everything worse. slowly."
        },
        {
          "role": "assistant",
          "content": "First, you take a deep breath. Then, you check in with your brother. Is he okay? Does he need anything right now? Just being there for him — that’s already helping.\n\nAfter that, you figure out what’s actually happened. What do you know for sure? Where was he driving from? Was there anyone else with him? Did he call someone? You don’t have to remember everything right away — just start with what you can.\n\nThen, you think about what needs to be done next. Maybe he needs to report the accident. Maybe he needs to talk to the police. Maybe there’s a lawyer involved. It might feel overwhelming, but you don’t have to do it all at once. Just take one thing at a time.\n\nAnd if you don’t know what to do — ask for help. You don’t have to figure this out alone. I’m here. You’re not in this by yourself."
        }
